In response to your message sent  28 May 1985 1139-PDT (Tuesday)

Having checked the error logs at ISIB and ISIF, I find that we have
rejected UDP packets for NPRDC, UCBMONET, EDN-VAX, and 18.71.0.21
because of UDP checksum problems.  I recently helped UCL squash a
similar bug in their use of BIND.

I would conjecture that there is a problem with UDP checksums in
BIND or some version(s) of UNIX.  Note that in the UCL case, they
could talk to other BINDs but no TOPS-20s, hence it would seem
that the UDP checksum is neither being produced nor checked.  I
seem to remember some discussion about such a UNIX problem a while
ago, but I'm not a UNIX person.

The ISI nameserver code does not support TCP use at present, and
hence ISIF, ISIB, and SRI-NIC don't.  Besides, it's a chance to use
datagrams before they are legislated extinct.

paul
